<file path="docs/standards/code-review-standard.md">
# Code Review Standard

Reviewers verify:

- architecture boundary compliance,
- tenancy safety,
- permission checks,
- entitlement correctness,
- idempotency/audit coverage,
- test coverage and naming consistency,
- no provider leakage into domain layer,
- no unapproved scope creep.
</file>

<file path="docs/standards/module-boundary-standard.md">
# Module Boundary Standard

- Every backend domain module must use `presentation/application/domain/infrastructure/tests`.
- Cross-module communication occurs through contracts, events, or explicit application interfaces.
- Direct cross-module DB writes are forbidden.
- Role-based modules (student/teacher/admin) are forbidden as backend boundaries.
</file>

<file path="docs/standards/naming-standard.md">
# Naming Standard

- Use domain-centric names, not team/role-centric names.
- Use kebab-case for folders, PascalCase for classes/types, camelCase for variables/functions.
- Event names follow `<domain>.<aggregate>.<action>.v<version>`.
- API endpoints are resource-oriented and tenant-aware.
</file>

<file path="docs/standards/observability-standard.md">
# Observability Standard

- Structured logs with correlation IDs.
- Trace critical request paths and async jobs.
- Emit domain-level metrics for throughput, error rates, and latency.
- Track policy denials and entitlement rejections.
- Alerting and SLOs evolve per environment maturity.
</file>

<file path="docs/standards/pull-request-standard.md">
# Pull Request Standard

- Keep scope focused and bounded.
- Link to requirement/issue.
- Include architecture impact note.
- Include tests and migration notes when relevant.
- Explicitly list non-goals and deferred items.
</file>

